parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or jerk while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the overdrive light blinks or stays on
and the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and gear shifting system can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the rear panel and frame can cause structural damage to the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear panel and frame show signs of rust
the rear hatch is fractured
and the vehicle's structural integrity is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and oil pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine knocks or makes unusual noises
the oil pressure drops
the engine stalls or loses power
and the vehicle's performance is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lift gate hinge can cause the glass to fall out of position, potentially causing injury or damage to the vehicle or surrounding objects.
symptoms: The rear lift gate hinge breaks or cracks
causing the glass to fall or become stuck in an open position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracked rear panel can cause water to seep into the vehicle, leading to rust and corrosion, and potentially causing electrical issues or other safety hazards.
symptoms: Vertical cracks appear on the rear panel
often near the Ford emblem
which can expand and contract with temperature changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause the vehicle to stall or run poorly, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Strong smell of rotten eggs
fuel system is too lean.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and timing chain issues can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Transmission is going out
timing chain and tensioners making loud knocking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate window hinge can cause the window to fall out, leading to property damage and potential injury to occupants or pedestrians.
symptoms: The hinge breaks or corrodes
causing the window to fall or become loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause it to fall and obstruct the driver's view, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The sun visor becomes detached or the clip breaks
causing it to dangle or fall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shattering of the rear window glass can cause injury to occupants or pedestrians and lead to property damage.
symptoms: The rear window glass shatters or explodes without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater blend door can cause the windshield to fog up, leading to reduced visibility and potential accidents.
symptoms: The heater blend door fails
causing the windshield to fog up.
